examples.en: The police took a calculated risk in releasing him.
He took a calculated risk and got in on the ground floor of the new enterprise.
The coach was calculated to carry six regular passengers.
He calculated the circumference of the circle.
We calculated that the trip would take two days.
Rates are calculated on an hourly basis.
Sally calculated that she'd have about 100 left.
We calculated the cost of new carpeting for the whole house.
Venice, that land so calculated to fire the imagination of a poet.
The numbers were calculated by reference to the most recent census.
Researchers calculated that this group was at a higher risk of heart disease.
He asked those pupils who calculated to join the musical school to come forward.
His speech was larded with words of praise calculated to win the crowd's support.
It was a calculated risk to appoint a man without management experience to such a senior post.
